    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen using multiprocessing Pool, the application hangs on get()\nIt will hang on close() also.\n\n\n### Code to reproduce the behaviour:\n\n```cython\n# example code\nimport multiprocessing as mp\n\n\ndef do_print(value):\n    print(value)\n    return f'Done {value}'\n\n\ndef main():\n    pool = mp.Pool(mp.cpu_count())\n\n    results = []\n\n    results.append(pool.apply_async(do_print, ['uno']))\n\n    for r in results:\n        print(r.get())\n\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    main()\n```\n\n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nOutput:\n```\nuno\nDone uno\n```\n\n\n### OS\n\nLinux Ubuntu 24.0.4 6.8.0-79-generic 79-Ubuntu SMP PREEMPT_DYNAMIC Tue Aug 12 14:42:46 UTC 2025 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Python version\n\n3.12.3\n\n### Cython version\n\n3.1.3, 3.0.8\n\n### Additional context\n\ncompilation:\n```bash\n  cython -3 --embed test.pyx\n  gcc -o test test.c -I /usr/include/python3.12 -Wl,-rpath,/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libpython3.12.so /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/libpython3.12.so\n```\n\n",
